    • Constructor Detail

      • HarvesterService

        public HarvesterService​(LocationRepository locationRepository,
                        HourlyPrecipitationRepository precipitationRepository,
                        HourlyWeatherRepository weatherRepository,
                        DocumentRequestService lrs,
                        Logger logger,
                        DateFormat harmonieDateFormat,
                        Executor executor)
        Creates an instance of HarvesterService.
        Parameters:
        locationRepository - The repository that stores the locations that data will be harvested for.
        precipitationRepository - The repository where precipitation data is stored.
        weatherRepository - The repository where non-precipitation weather data is stored.
        lrs - The service that is used to obtain XML weather data documents for locations.
        logger - Logs warning messages and exceptions.
        harmonieDateFormat - Used to parse date data using a given time zone.
        executor - Used to execute the data harvesting process on a thread.

      • fetchAndStore

        @PreAuthorize("#ownedItem.hasOwner(authentication.name)")
public void fetchAndStore​(Location ownedItem)
                   throws HarvestParseException,
                          HarvestRequestException,
                          DocumentNotFoundException
        Requests and stores weather data from a HARMONIE-AROME API for a given location.
        Parameters:
        ownedItem - The location to obtain data for.
        Throws:
        HarvestParseException - Thrown if there was a SAX exception when parsing.
        HarvestRequestException - Thrown if there was an I/O exception when connecting to the URI.
        DocumentNotFoundException - Thrown if there was no XML document found at the URI.
